1
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:12,633
<i>Boss Logan wants you
to have this.</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:13,933
<i> To help you relax.</i>

3
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:15,700
<i>- What's this?
- Hallucinogen.</i>

4
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,333
<i> It works perfectly with wine.</i>

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,900
<i>- I miss you so much, Emma.
- I miss you so much.</i>

6
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:22,267
<i> I don't understand mom.</i>

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,600
<i>Didn't she say nothing was
going on between her and Logan?</i>

8
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,300
<i> So, what did we see?</i>

9
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:28,333
<i>- I'm done!
- Jade, wait!</i>

10
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>I don't want to talk
about that woman anymore.</i>

11
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:33,733
<i>I've noticed lately
that she has many red flags.</i>

12
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:35,267
<i>She's behaving like Mommy Olive.</i>

13
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,800
<i>Are you able to call
grandmother?</i>

14
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:38,333
<i>Do you communicate
with her?</i>

15
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:41,733
<i>Jade was the last person
Ligaya talked to.</i>

16
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:42,933
<i>- Correct?
- Yes.</i>

17
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:44,733
<i>Don't you think
that witch did something</i>

18
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> to your grandmother?</i>

19
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:46,833
<i> It was Danilo who went in.</i>

20
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:47,933
<i> How could it be Danilo?</i>

21
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,967
<i>You can see clearly
that it's Boss Logan.</i>

22
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:51,533
<i> How did that happen?</i>

23
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:53,833
<i> The wine that Logan sent me.</i>

24
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:55,133
<i>Jade was the last person
Ligaya talked to.</i>

25
00:01:55,267 --> 00:01:56,967
<i>- Correct?
- Yes.</i>

26
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,667
<i>Don't you think that witch
did something</i>

27
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,100
<i> to your grandmother?</i>

28
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:07,500
Baby girl!

29
00:02:07,633 --> 00:02:09,033
You're home.

30
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:13,667
Don't stay up too late.

31
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,300
We'll have our final fitting
early tomorrow.

32
00:02:16,467 --> 00:02:19,000
- Love, here's your beer.
- Thank you.

33
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:21,900
Mommy Jade, I'm just curious.

34
00:02:22,033 --> 00:02:24,367
Who will walk you to the altar?

35
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,633
Well, I was thinking of you.

36
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:31,500
But then, you're already
my maid of honor,

37
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:35,433
so I'll walk down
the aisle alone.

38
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:40,200
Why not Grandmother Ligaya?

39
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,700
She's right, Jade.

40
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:45,000
She had enough time to cool off.

41
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,800
She's probably...

42
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:48,667
not upset with us anymore.

43
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,033
No.

44
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:53,167
I don't even know
where that woman is.

45
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,133
What?

46
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,767
Weren't you the one
she last talked to?

47
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:01,600
And didn't you tell me
she was in Cebu?

48
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:02,800
Yes, yes.

49
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:09,733
She told me she was in Cebu,
but not exactly where.

50
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:14,400
And I haven't talked to her
again since that day.

51
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:17,233
Aren't you worried about her?

52
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:19,533
Because I'm starting
to get worried.

53
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,667
Baby girl,

54
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,200
I'm sure your
grandmother's just upset.

55
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,000
But I don't think
that's a good enough reason

56
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:31,533
for you not to find out
where she is.

57
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,167
Can we stop talking

58
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,433
- about that woman?
- Jade, Jade, Jade!

59
00:03:36,567 --> 00:03:38,300
Don't yell at Mookie.

60
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:42,967
I'm so sorry, baby girl.

61
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:43,933
Dan.

62
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:46,167
Dan, I'm so sorry.

63
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,033
I didn't mean it.

64
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:50,833
You know, I'm so stressed.

65
00:03:50,967 --> 00:03:53,833
In just a few days,
we'll be getting married.

66
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,867
So, can we just please
focus on that?

67
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:01,767
Your grandmother will come back
once she has forgiven us.

68
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,700
Can we not think
about her for now,

69
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,133
and let's just focus
on the wedding?

70
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:07,333
Please.

71
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:21,067
I'm so sorry, baby girl.

72
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,367
Get some rest. Go on.

73
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,633
Go, Mookie.

74
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,600
Good night, sweetheart.

75
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,200
Hey.

76
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:16,733
What are you doing here?

77
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:17,967
What's going on?

78
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,500
What did you do at the bar
the night Danilo came?

79
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:25,633
What?

80
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:27,667
What's the matter?
What did I do?

81
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,667
You sent me a glass of wine.

82
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,900
I got drunk.

83
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:35,300
You put something on the wine.
What is it?

84
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,833
What did you put on the wine?

85
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,067
Nothing!

86
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,600
There was!

87
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:47,800
I saw you on the CCTV
coming into the office.

88
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:50,233
But I saw Danilo instead.

89
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,533
Emma,

90
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:54,100
I didn't put
anything on the wine!

91
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:56,933
You did!
There has to be something!

92
00:05:57,067 --> 00:05:58,600
It's just a glass of wine.

93
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:01,467
I wouldn't get drunk
if you didn't put anything!

94
00:06:09,233 --> 00:06:10,167
Okay.

95
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,500
Okay, I'm sorry.

96
00:06:13,733 --> 00:06:14,967
I'm sorry.

97
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:18,433
I only did that because...

98
00:06:20,233 --> 00:06:22,267
I don't want you
to go back to Danilo.

99
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,400
Emma, I love you so much.

100
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:29,067
Just choose me.

101
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:32,567
I will love you
more than Danilo does.

102
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:33,967
I'll give you everything!

103
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:36,067
- Everything you want...
- Darn you!

104
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,600
You fooled me!
I thought we were friends!

105
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:41,567
I thought I could trust you!

106
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:44,033
Okay, fine!

107
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:45,333
I'm a bastard.

108
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,867
But Jade was right.

109
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
She deserves to be with Danilo.

110
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:53,333
And I deserve to be with you!

111
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:54,567
What did you say?

112
00:06:56,133 --> 00:06:58,233
What does Jade have to do
with this?

113
00:06:58,367 --> 00:06:59,967
Are you two talking?

114
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:02,567
What?

115
00:07:03,367 --> 00:07:04,567
Answer me!

116
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,300
What are you two talking about?

117
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:09,533
Are you talking about
how to separate me and Danilo?

118
00:07:09,667 --> 00:07:12,400
Is that why you put something
on the wine that you gave me?

119
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:16,033
Does Jade have something
to do with this?

120
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,967
Does she?

121
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:18,967
Emma.

122
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:22,933
Darn you!

123
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,600
Now I understand
why no one loves you!

124
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,467
You play dirty!

125
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,000
Bastard!

126
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:32,733
That's enough!

127
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:34,100
Stop!

128
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:40,433
After everything
I did for you...

129
00:07:41,467 --> 00:07:43,600
is this what you'll repay me?

130
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:49,433
I've never forgotten
all the help you've given me.

131
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:54,167
But I didn't know you were
also evil like Olive and Jade.

132
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,833
That's why Jade, who's also
a monster, couldn't love you.

133
00:07:57,967 --> 00:08:00,100
Because you're
a worthless person!

134
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:01,367
Stop!

135
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,333
Go ahead.

136
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:03,733
Do it!

137
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,533
Hello?

138
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:00,733
<i> Is anyone there?</i>

139
00:09:06,867 --> 00:09:08,133
Hello?

140
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:12,300
<i> Is there someone here?</i>

141
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:18,833
Grandmother?

142
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:20,167
Grandmother, is that you?

143
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:26,567
Grandmother?

144
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,200
- Mookie?
- Grandmother...

145
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:42,833
What's in that room, Mommy Jade?

146
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:45,200
Oh, nothing.

147
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:47,233
Just my personal
belongings.

148
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,967
Can I see it?

149
00:09:51,267 --> 00:09:56,967
Baby girl, as much as I want to
share a lot of things with you,

150
00:09:57,100 --> 00:10:00,400
there should still
be boundaries. Right?

151
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:04,100
There are things
that I cannot share with you.

152
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:07,433
Let's go.

153
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:10,500
Private things?

154
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:12,000
Or...

155
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:13,300
secrets?

156
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,133
Secrets?

157
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:18,000
What are you saying?

158
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:20,133
What would I hide from you?

159
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:22,767
I don't know.

160
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,567
About grandmother?

161
00:10:27,267 --> 00:10:30,467
You were the last one
who talked to her. Right?

162
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:36,300
Maybe there's something
you don't want to share.

163
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:41,667
I don't understand
what you mean, sweetie.

164
00:10:43,167 --> 00:10:44,933
I really don't know anything.

165
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:48,000
All I know
is that she's in Cebu.

166
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:50,367
And that's what you know,
too, right?

167
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,800
But, Mommy Jade,

168
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,567
something doesn't feel right.

169
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:57,800
You don't seem to be bothered

170
00:10:57,933 --> 00:11:00,200
that we don't hear anything
about grandmother.

171
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:10,467
You know what? My mom can't rest
until she finds grandmother

172
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:12,800
in one of the gambling dens
in our area.

173
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:17,933
Can we not talk about Emma?

174
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:24,267
I'm sorry, baby girl.

175
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,400
It's just that...

176
00:11:27,533 --> 00:11:29,767
you're acting quite different.

177
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:31,100
What's with you?

178
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,600
You know,

179
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:39,467
I could no longer find
the key to that room.

180
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,800
It's been a long time
since I opened that.

181
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:46,933
Please...

182
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:51,200
stop thinking
about all sorts of things.

183
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:52,900
In roughly two days,

184
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:55,067
your dad and I will get married.

185
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,400
We'll be a family.

186
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:00,433
Do we really want to have
a misunderstanding now?

187
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:04,567
Good.

188
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,100
Get some rest.

189
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,000
We have an early fitting
tomorrow.

190
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,400
Okay?

191
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,300
Okay.

192
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:12,767
- Good night, baby girl.
- Good night.

193
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:50,433
Mister, please wait for me.

194
00:12:58,233 --> 00:12:59,600
Dan!

195
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,833
Dan! Mookie!

196
00:13:01,967 --> 00:13:03,133
Danilo!

197
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,467
Danilo! Mookie!

198
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,800
Dan!

199
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,267
You can't come inside.

200
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,867
Mister, I'll just talk
to my husband and daughter.

201
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,400
I'm really sorry,
but you can't come inside.

202
00:13:17,533 --> 00:13:19,300
It's important. I just really
need to talk to them.

203
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:20,500
It won't take long. Please.

204
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,667
- I'm begging you.
- You can't go in, Ma'am.

205
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:22,867
Please.

206
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,967
Danilo!

207
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,533
Mookie!

208
00:13:25,667 --> 00:13:26,533
Dan!

209
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:27,900
Dan!

210
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:30,833
- Danilo!
- Mister, it's okay. Let her in.

211
00:13:32,067 --> 00:13:34,367
Let's go, Emma. Come with me.

212
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:47,000
Maybe we should add more here.

213
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:49,133
- Perfect.
- Yes.

214
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:51,033
Let's trim this part a bit.

215
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:53,900
Is this okay with you, Ma'am?

216
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:55,700
- Yes.
- Let's trim it here.

217
00:13:55,867 --> 00:13:58,700
Yes, just a little bit.

218
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:00,700
Hi, Emma!

219
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:03,433
Excuse me. Please excuse us.

220
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:05,933
So, Emma, what do you think?

221
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:07,900
Do you like it?

222
00:14:08,033 --> 00:14:09,500
Your wedding is still on?

223
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:10,833
Of course!

224
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:13,467
I was so happy
when I saw you on the CCTV.

225
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,100
So I told Astrid to let you in.

226
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:20,167
And finally, I can give
this to you in person.

227
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:22,633
Astrid, can you please
hand me that?

228
00:14:24,433 --> 00:14:26,233
Thank you.

229
00:14:26,367 --> 00:14:28,367
Here you go, Emma.

230
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,133
Don't miss it, Sis, okay?

231
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:43,467
Astrid made sure to reserve
the best spot for you.

232
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,967
Of course, in front.

233
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,767
So you won't miss anything
at the ceremony.

234
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,300
I won't let
your wedding happen.

235
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:58,067
Really, Emma?

236
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,000
So what are you going to do?

237
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:01,533
Let me guess.

238
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:03,667
A.

239
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,967
You'll be rolling
on the floor.

240
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,500
B.

241
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:10,467
You'll beg Danilo.

242
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,633
Which one?

243
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:15,767
I'll tell Danilo
what you and Logan did to me.

244
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:19,367
You two conspired.

245
00:15:20,567 --> 00:15:22,233
Oh my gosh, Emma.

246
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,100
You're having an episode again.

247
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:26,633
Don't touch me!

248
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:29,300
Have you been taking your meds?

249
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:31,133
Emma.

250
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:33,500
Take your medicine.

251
00:15:33,633 --> 00:15:36,300
I need to talk
to Danilo and Mookie.

252
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:37,633
Dan!

253
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,200
- Dan!
- Oh, please.

254
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,233
- Hey!
- Danilo!

255
00:15:40,367 --> 00:15:42,133
Don't step on my dress!
What are you doing?

256
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:43,367
Danilo! Dan!

257
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,433
- Guard, bring this woman out.
- Danilo!

258
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:47,400
She's making a scene
on my property!

259
00:15:47,533 --> 00:15:49,733
- Emma, please leave.
- Astrid, come on!

260
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:51,867
- Please go.
- Bring her out.

261
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,367
Dan!

262
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,500
Mookie!

263
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:56,933
Dan!

264
00:16:02,133 --> 00:16:05,100
Jade, was it really necessary
to let her in

265
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:07,833
only to have her drag out?

266
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Oh, come on, Astrid.

267
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:10,967
I just want to have
a little fun with her.

268
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,833
Where's your humor?

269
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,400
By the way,

270
00:16:17,533 --> 00:16:18,800
where's Mookie?

271
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,300
- Mookie!
- Ma'am...

272
00:16:21,433 --> 00:16:23,433
I just ran into her
a while ago.

273
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:24,467
Where did she go?

274
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,867
I think she went
to the basement.

275
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:31,133
What?

276
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:33,167
Remove this dress! Hurry!

277
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,967
Remove this gown now!

278
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:39,700
Remove my shoes, too! Faster!

279
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:42,733
Stop!

280
00:16:45,133 --> 00:16:46,300
Wait! I need to go inside.

281
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:48,500
I'll talk to my husband
and daughter.

282
00:16:48,633 --> 00:16:51,167
- Dan!
- Ma'am, don't be stubborn.

283
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:52,467
I won't stay long!

284
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,767
Danilo!

285
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,133
Dan!

286
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:57,367
Ma'am, please don't be stubborn.

287
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,467
Emma?

288
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:01,767
What are you doing here?

289
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:05,767
Dan. Dan, please let's talk.

290
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,533
The nerve of you!

291
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:08,800
Don't you feel any shame?

292
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,400
After we saw you doing nasty
things with your lover,

293
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:16,500
you had the nerve to show up
to me and my daughter.

294
00:17:16,667 --> 00:17:18,400
That's why I'm here to explain.

295
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:19,600
No need, Emma!

296
00:17:20,667 --> 00:17:24,067
Because I know,
you'll just mess with my head.

297
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,500
You will only hurt
my daughter again.

298
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:28,933
She's affected by it, Emma.

299
00:17:29,067 --> 00:17:32,100
Mookie doesn't say anything, but
I can see that she's struggling.

300
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:33,433
She's hurting.

301
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:36,300
Because you keep betraying her!

302
00:17:37,567 --> 00:17:40,100
Emma, you have no shame.

303
00:17:40,233 --> 00:17:43,800
Dan, can you listen to me
before you insult me?

304
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:45,900
Logan put a drug on my drink.

305
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:50,000
I thought I was with you, but
it turns out that it was him.

306
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:53,300
And now you're blaming
your lover.

307
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:56,633
I don't believe you anymore,
Emma.

308
00:17:56,767 --> 00:18:00,700
At first, you accused Jade
of driving you insane.

309
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:03,600
And now,
your lover is drugging you?

310
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,000
That's the truth!

311
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:06,733
And Jade has something
to do with it.

312
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:09,300
Emma, you keep telling
the same story!

313
00:18:10,367 --> 00:18:11,067
Fine.

314
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,467
Let's say Logan
really did that,

315
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,167
and he was in cahoots with Jade.

316
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:17,667
Now what?

317
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,267
Where's your proof?

318
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,133
Show me.

319
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:25,400
Show me your proof.
I might believe you.

320
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:28,000
- Dan.
- What?

321
00:18:28,133 --> 00:18:29,367
Dan, please believe me.

322
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:30,967
- I'm telling you the truth.
- You don't have proof.

323
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,000
You have no proof.

324
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:33,567
- You better go home.
- Dan, wait.

325
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:35,033
Go home. You're wasting my time.

326
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,600
Go home!

327
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,233
Guard, please open the gate.

328
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:10,133
Boss, you look like
a lovestruck teen,

329
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:13,633
with the teddy bear, flowers,
and all.

330
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:17,433
Marco...

331
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:19,367
do you want to lose your job?

332
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:22,367
Shut up.

333
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,833
You might spoil
my surprise for Emma.

334
00:19:26,067 --> 00:19:27,900
Do you think I normally do this?

335
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:30,300
I made an effort.
So don't ruin it.

336
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:34,300
Open the door.

337
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:36,567
So you can be useful.

338
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:47,867
Move.

339
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,367
Emma, I have...

340
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:53,033
Emma?

341
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:56,900
Emma?

342
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:01,600
Emma?

343
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:14,167
Boss, what did it say?

344
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:17,933
She resigned from work.

345
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:21,400
She quit.

346
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,033
This can't happen.

347
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:30,433
Here you go, Emma. Come in.

348
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:32,500
Let me have that one.
Let me help you.

349
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:34,033
Come on.

350
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:35,700
Sit down first.

351
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:41,067
My place is small and stuffy.

352
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,900
Flor, thank you.

353
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,633
Don't worry, this is only
temporary.

354
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:46,700
I'll find a place to stay.

355
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,867
Come on. It's not a big deal.

356
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:52,700
We can share if you like. So...

357
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:55,033
I can cut down on my expenses.

358
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:56,600
Really? Sure.

359
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:59,100
You can go with me and look
for a bigger apartment.

360
00:20:59,233 --> 00:21:00,767
Oh, sure. I'd love that.

361
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:01,833
Yes.

362
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:06,767
- Are you comfortable there?
- Yes.

363
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,767
Marco...

364
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,133
find her.

365
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,100
Boss, where would I find her?

366
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,533
I don't know!

367
00:21:22,667 --> 00:21:23,933
I have no idea! Do something!

368
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,967
How can you find someone
who doesn't want to be found?

369
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:27,967
Just...

370
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,467
find her!

371
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,433
Get out of here!
You're annoying me!

372
00:21:37,567 --> 00:21:38,700
You know what, Flor,

373
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:43,067
Danilo wasn't convinced that
Logan put something on my wine.

374
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,267
And he also didn't believe

375
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:47,133
that Jade and Logan
were in cahoots.

376
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:49,767
He wants me to prove
my innocence.

377
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,700
Why should I do that?

378
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,300
I'm telling the truth.

379
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:55,600
Come on.

380
00:21:55,733 --> 00:21:58,200
That's how the world works,
right?

381
00:21:58,333 --> 00:22:02,533
We always have
to prove ourselves.

382
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:04,300
But, go.

383
00:22:04,433 --> 00:22:07,267
Prove to Danilo that
you're telling the truth.

384
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:10,033
So he can stop doubting you.

385
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:11,167
But...

386
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:13,600
that's not going to be easy.

387
00:22:13,733 --> 00:22:14,767
Why?

388
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:18,767
Emma, he's going to marry
your evil sister tomorrow.

389
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:20,400
So how?

390
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:22,900
You only have one day to prove

391
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:26,867
that Jade and Boss Logan
are working together.

392
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:56,633
Mookie!

393
00:22:56,767 --> 00:22:57,733
No!

394
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,033
Mookie!

395
00:23:05,167 --> 00:23:05,600
No!

396
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:10,067
Mookie, no!

397
00:23:23,133 --> 00:23:24,400
What's this?

398
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:26,367
A porn collection?

399
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,800
No.

400
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:29,667
That can't be.

401
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,600
What's wrong, baby girl?

402
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:34,300
Why do you look so disappointed?

403
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:37,867
Were you expecting
to see something else?

404
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,200
Are you a porn addict, Jade?

405
00:23:47,567 --> 00:23:49,967
Shut the hell up, Astrid.

406
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,333
Yes!

407
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:57,767
I'm a porn addict.

408
00:23:57,900 --> 00:23:59,133
I'm into it.

409
00:23:59,267 --> 00:24:00,100
Happy?

410
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:01,467
Okay?

411
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,433
I'm not really proud of it,

412
00:24:05,567 --> 00:24:06,800
but...

413
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:10,067
I got into it
while I was in Japan.

414
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,600
And this is the reason

415
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:15,100
why I don't want you
to go inside this room, Mookie.

416
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:19,367
Because this is very,
very personal and private.

417
00:24:21,367 --> 00:24:22,900
But...

418
00:24:23,033 --> 00:24:26,400
you think all sorts of things
about me.

419
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:27,633
So there...

420
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:34,967
My secret that only I
was supposed to know

421
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:37,167
is now out in the open.

422
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:38,900
You already know about it.

423
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:43,400
I know you're thinking ill
about me.

424
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,033
I know you're suspecting...

425
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:51,167
that I'm hiding mom
in this room.

426
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:53,467
Mookie...

427
00:24:55,067 --> 00:24:57,567
what made you think
that I can do that?

428
00:25:00,767 --> 00:25:02,467
I'm not like your mom.

429
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,800
I'm not like Olive.

430
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:10,500
I'm not a bad person, Mookie.

431
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,600
<i> Grandmother?</i>

432
00:25:14,733 --> 00:25:16,067
<i>- Mookie?
- Grandmother?</i>

433
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:21,933
<i> I need you to do something.</i>

434
00:25:22,067 --> 00:25:24,133
<i> I've been waiting for you.</i>

435
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:26,533
<i> Why did you come so late?</i>

436
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:29,533
<i>You told me
to look for x-rated films.</i>

437
00:25:29,667 --> 00:25:32,067
<i>I even bothered my friends
to buy their collection.</i>

438
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,067
<i> Fine.</i>

439
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,867
<i> You make too many excuses.</i>

440
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:41,967
<i> Do you see this?</i>

441
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:47,633
<i> I'm sure you'll like this.</i>

442
00:25:47,767 --> 00:25:49,300
<i> This will calm you down.</i>

443
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:00,067
You know what?

444
00:26:01,733 --> 00:26:03,600
I feel so betrayed.

445
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:09,933
I don't know why
you're suspecting me like this.

446
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,600
You didn't even believe me,

447
00:26:12,733 --> 00:26:14,133
and on top of that,
you disrespected me.

448
00:26:14,267 --> 00:26:17,433
And worse, you humiliated me.

449
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:23,000
I don't know what I did
to you to suspect me.

450
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:33,533
Mommy Jade...

451
00:26:33,667 --> 00:26:35,533
I'm sorry.

452
00:26:35,667 --> 00:26:37,733
I'm really sorry.

453
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,433
Of course, I forgive you.

454
00:26:47,567 --> 00:26:48,633
Don't look at that.

455
00:26:48,767 --> 00:26:50,933
It's not for you, Dear.

456
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:52,200
It's okay.

457
00:27:05,867 --> 00:27:07,433
She's mine to begin with.

458
00:27:07,567 --> 00:27:09,533
So why would I give her
back to you?

459
00:27:09,667 --> 00:27:11,033
Where are you taking
my daughter?

460
00:27:11,167 --> 00:27:13,067
<i> In their final battle...</i>

461
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:16,900
What if she is the one
who forgets you?

462
00:27:17,067 --> 00:27:19,533
<i> Who will walk away in tears?</i>

463
00:27:19,667 --> 00:27:21,733
- Let go of our daughter.
- Take one step closer

464
00:27:21,867 --> 00:27:23,567
and Mookie's head blows up!

465
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:24,533
No!

466
00:27:24,667 --> 00:27:26,500
<i> Is it going to be...</i>

467
00:27:26,633 --> 00:27:28,800
Dear, get well soon.

468
00:27:28,933 --> 00:27:30,400
Will you still marry me, Emma?

469
00:27:30,533 --> 00:27:32,200
<i> a happy ending?</i>

470
00:27:32,333 --> 00:27:35,067
<i> Mommy Dearest, finale week!</i>
